# Learning How To Learn: How to become a better learner

* Exercise stimulates neuron-creation
  - Neurons are essential for learning new things, and will die if unused.
* Building knowledge is not linear
  - You may find that your understanding seems to go backwards at times, but it is a sign that your brain is restructuring the information in order to build on existing knowledge.
* Create lively visual metaphors or analogies
  - All metaphors and analogies break down at some point but they can provide excellent memory, visual or conceptual aids.
* "Genius" can be achieved by practicing good learning techniques, don't be fooled by imposter syndrome.
* Working in teams has many benefits
  - Explaining ideas to others helps you think more coherently
  - Peers can 'reality-check' your assumptions
  - Different people have different ideas and insights


